<LP>
   PUBLISHING: Ziff Communications, a large publisher of
computer magazines, formed a new division, Ziff-Davis Press,
to publish computer-related books. It will publish its first
titles in the first quarter of 1991 in conjunction with PC
Magazine.
                                                                                                       

</LP>
<TEXT>
   OLYMPICS: Westwood One Inc.'s NBC Radio Networks unit
received exclusive rights to broadcast the 1992 Summer
Olympics in Barcelona, Spain, to U.S. radio audiences in
English. Westwood also will provide promotional opportunities
for the Olympics on its other outlets.
                                                                                                       

   WHO'S NEWS: MCA Inc. said Jon Gumpert was named senior
vice president of legal and business affairs for its
Universal Pictures unit. He was executive vice president of
Odyssey Entertainment Ltd.
